U.S. Submarine Tender to Support AUKUS Pillar 1 Milestone

HMAS STIRLING, Australia - The U.S. Navy submarine tender USS Emory S. Land (AS 39) pulled into HMAS Stirling, Aug. 16, marking the seventh port visit in Australia since the ship left its homeport of Guam, May 17.

U.S. Second Fleet Joins Multinational Partners for Operation Nanook 2024

HALIFAX, Nova Scotia - U.S. Second Fleet’s Arleigh Burke-class destroyer, USS Delbert D. Black (DDG 119), departed Halifax, Canada August 15, 2024, to join maritime partners from Canada, Denmark, and the U.S. Coast Guard for Operation Nanook 2024.

Navy Medicine Enterprise established to support readiness and warfighting

FALLS CHURCH, Va. - Vice Chief of Naval Operations Adm. Jim Kilby approved the establishment of the Navy Medicine Enterprise (NME), which is an operationally focused organizational structure providing senior fleet leadership a mechanism to address and prioritize health service support

Top Naval Safety Experts Convene to Enhance Incident Reporting

NAVAL STATION NORFOLK, Va. – More than 60 safety experts from across the naval enterprise convened here August 7-8 to improve the Department of the Navy’s Risk Management Information (RMI) system. Hosted by the Naval Safety Command (NAVSAFECOM), participants tackled pressing safety

Walter Reed Offers Partial Hospitalization Program for Mental Health Care

BETHESDA, Md. - Walter Reed offers the Partial Hospitalization Program (PHP), providing support and skills to assist people in managing their behavioral health challenges while living at home.

Ideas in Flight: ONR TechSolutions Delivers New Realistic Flight Simulator

ARLINGTON, Va. - A new innovation in aviation training, featuring a simulator sponsored by the Office of Naval Research TechSolutions program, delivers a better way to prepare future Navy pilots.The T-45C Goshawk mixed-reality simulator, also known as Project Link, was recently showcased at Naval

U.S., France Naval Forces Conduct Bilateral Operations in Indo-Pacific

PHILIPPINE SEA - The U.S. Navy and French Navy joined forces to conduct bilateral operations in support of a free and open Indo-Pacific in the Philippine Sea, Aug. 13.

NIWC Atlantic Engineer Honors Legacy of Great-Grandfather on Navajo Code Talker Day

JOINT BASE Charleston, S.C. - As the United States observes National Navajo Code Talkers Day on August 14, a significant moment of remembrance and tribute unfolds at Naval Information Warfare Center (NIWC) Atlantic.
